Peanut Sauce Butter Beans
  --Deborah Murphy

1/2 c creamy peanut butter
1/2 c water
3 tbsp reduced sodium shoyu
1 tbsp toasted sesame oil
1/2 tbsp sriracha 
1/2" ginger, grated
2 cloves garlic, minced
15 oz jar butter beans, drained and rinsed
1/2 lime, juiced

Add the peanut butter, water, shoyu, sesame oil, sriracha, ginger, and garlic to a skillet over medium heat. Bring to a simmer and whisk for 2-3 min or until thick and creamy. Add the butter beans and stir well to coat in sauce. Cook for another 2-3 min to warm up the beans. Garnish with chili crisp, cilantro, and sesame seeds. Serve with naan or pita for dipping or scoop into a bowl with rice and veggies.
